What you need to know:

Reiterating his ambition to become Kenya’s fifth President, the Amani National Congress (ANC) leader asked the community to support him.The politician, who was accompanied by Kajiado Governor Joseph ole Lenku, spoke of a long lasting, cordial relationship with the people of that county and the larger Maasai community.Mr Mudavadi also reaffirmed his support for President Uhuru Kenyatta in the fight against corruption.